%20truck%20%E2%80%94%20we%20offered%20to%20sell%20him%20a%20used%20Toyota%20Camry%20that%20would%20meet%20all%20his%20needs%2C%20but%20he%20spent%20%2470%2C000%20on%20a%20truck.%20I%20know%20the%20truck%20cost%20that%20much%20because%20he%20bragged%20about%20it%20to%20his%20dad%20after%20he%20turned%20down%20our%20offer%20to%20sell%20him%20the%20Toyota%20for%20a%20great%20price.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20made%20that%20offer%20because%20we%20are%20worried%20about%20his%20financial%20choices%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20feel%20comfortable%20coming%20out%20and%20telling%20him%20that%20spending%20%2470%2C000%20on%20a%20truck%20when%20you're%20anything%20less%20than%20a%20millionaire%20rancher%20is%20a%20stupid%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20we%20tell%20him%20and%20his%20wife%20to%20slow%20down%3F%20Should%20we%20just%20mind%20our%20own%20business%20until%20he's%20drowning%20in%20debt%3F%20He%20might%20be%20an%20adult%2C%20but%20he'll%20always%20be%20my%20son%2C%20and%20it%20hurts%20me%20to%20watch%20him%20go%20down%20this%20path.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOnce%20a%20Worried%20Mom%2C%20Always%20a%20Worried%20Mom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Worried%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20spent%20the%20last%20four%20years%20of%20my%20life%20learning%20everything%20there%20is%20to%20know%20about%20getting%20into%20an%20Ivy%20League%20school%2C%20because%20my%20driven%20A%2B%20daughter%20wants%20to%20attend%20Harvard.%20I've%20ensured%20both%20of%20us%20are%20doing%20everything%20possible%20to%20improve%20her%20chances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20my%20daughter%20is%20in%207th%20grade.%20At%20any%20point%20in%20the%20next%20six%20years%2C%20she%20could%20meet%20a%20guy%20she%20can't%20bear%20to%20leave%2C%20decide%20to%20skip%20college%20altogether%2C%20or%20follow%20her%20high%20school%20friends%20to%20a%20state%20school.%20Even%20writing%20these%20things%20is%20semi-devastating.%20If%20there%20was%20ever%20a%20middle-class%2C%20public%20school%20kid%20from%20the%20suburban%20Midwest%20with%20a%20chance%20at%20Harvard%2C%20it's%20my%20daughter.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20her%20waste%20her%20talent.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20her%20sacrifice%20her%20dreams%20on%20the%20altar%20of%20a%20relationship%20or%20compromise%20her%20future%20for%20a%20passing%20fancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20chooses%20to%20do%20these%20things%2C%20however%2C%20there's%20nothing%20I%20can%20do.%20This%20is%20her%20life.%20And%20while%20I%20can%20encourage%20and%20support%20her%20as%20hard%20as%20I%20can%20in%20the%20direction%20I%20think%20she%20should%20go%2C%20chances%20are%2C%20all%20that%20will%20do%20is%20alienate%20her.%20But%20knowing%20this%20doesn't%20make%20it%20any%20less%20painful.%20As%20Elizabeth%20Stone%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BMaking%20the%20decision%20to%20have%20a%20child%20%E2%80%A6%20is%20to%20decide%20forever%20to%20have%20your%20heart%20go%20walking%20around%20outside%20your%20body.%26quot%3B%20All%20we%20want%20for%20our%20hearts%20walking%20around%20out%20of%20our%20bodies%20is%20safety%2C%20happiness%2C%20and%20success.%20Nothing%20will%20change%20that.%20Nothing%20should%20change%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20something%20must%20temper%20it%2C%20because%20our%20children%20aren't%20actually%20our%20hearts.%20They%20aren't%20extensions%20of%20us%20at%20all.%20They%20are%20whole%20human%20beings%20who%20deserve%20to%20choose%20their%20own%20paths%20and%20make%20their%20own%20mistakes.%20Even%20%2470%2C000%20mistakes.%20Even%20%2470%2C000%20mistakes%20that%20end%20up%20with%20upside-down%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20repo%20men%20in%20the%20driveway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20son%20deserves%20the%20opportunity%20to%20make%20his%20own%20choices%2C%20b